# Video2Doc

This project aims to convert video content into documentation.

## Getting Started

## Prerequisites
- Python 3.8 or higher
- FFmpeg installed on your system
- CUDA-compatible GPU (optional, for faster processing)

## Installation
1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Video2Doc.git
cd Video2Doc
```

2. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Features
- Video transcription using state-of-the-art speech recognition
- Automatic section detection and formatting
- Support for multiple video formats
- Markdown output with proper formatting
- Code block detection and syntax highlighting

## Usage
```python
from video2doc import VideoConverter

converter = VideoConverter("input_video.mp4")
converter.generate_doc("output.md")
```

